#MEM id=references source=/root/yvon/agent-department/COO/diana/skills/marketplace/traction-eos/references/people.md savings=4%
M|Peop|tx|The People cp is where most entrepreneurial companies struggle the hardest. Having the right people in the right seats is the single biggest factor in a company's ability to execute its vision. This guide covers the Accountability Chart, the Visionary/Integrator dynamic, the People Analyzer, GWC assessment, and practical frameworks for making difficult people decisions.
M|The |tx|The Accountability Chart is not an org chart. An org chart shows hierarchy and reporting lines. An Accountability Chart shows the major functions of the business and who is accountable for each fn's results.
M|Why |tx|\| Org Chart \| Accountability Chart \|
M|Why |tx|\|-----------\|---------------------\|
M|Why |tx|\| Shows who reports to whom \| Shows who owns what outcomes \|
M|Why |tx|\| People-centric \| fn-centric \|
M|Why |tx|\| Grows w/ headcount \| Stays simple (5-7 major functions) \|
M|Why |tx|\| Can mask shared accountability \| Enforces single-point accountability \|
M|Buil|**St|Start w/ the Three Major Functions**
M|Buil|Ever|
M|Buil|tx|```
M|Buil|tx|Visionary ←→ Integrator
M|Buil|tx|\|
M|Buil|tx|┌──────────────┼──────────────┐
M|Buil|tx|\|              \|              \|
M|Buil|tx|Sales/mk  Operations     fi
M|Buil|tx|```
M|Buil|**St|Define 3-5 Accountabilities per fn**
M|Buil|tx|Each major fn has specific outcomes it is responsible for. Write these as bullet points under each seat.
M|Buil|tx|\| fn \| Key Accountabilities \|
M|Buil|tx|\|----------\|---------------------\|
M|Buil|tx|\| **Sales/mk** \| rv targets, lead generation, br management, cs acquisition, sales process \|
M|Buil|tx|\| **Operations** \| Service/pd delivery, qual assurance, project management, cs satisfaction, capacity planning \|
M|Buil|tx|\| **fi** \| Financial reporting, cash flow management, budgeting, legal compliance, risk management \|
M|Buil|**St|Add Custom Functions if Needed**
M|Buil|Some|
M|Buil|it|**Technology/Engineering** (for pd companies)
M|Buil|it|**People/HR** (for companies w/ 50+ employees)
M|Buil|it|**cs sc** (for subscription businesses)
M|Buil|**St|Name the Seat, Then Fill It**
M|Buil|tx|ds the Accountability Chart for the company you need, not the company you have. Determine the right structure first, then identify who shd fill each seat. Sometimes one person holds multiple seats (common in smaller companies). That is fine as long as it is explicit.
M|The |Ever|
M|The |it|Neither feels fully responsible
M|The |it|Conflicts go unresolved
M|The |it|Results suffer
M|The |tx|When two people argue abt who owns a fn, the Integrator decides.
M|Visi|tx|The two most important seats in any EOS company are the Visionary and the Integrator. These roles are complementary and must work in partnership.
M|Role|tx|\| Dimension \| Visionary \| Integrator \|
M|Role|tx|\|-----------\|-----------\|------------\|
M|Role|tx|\| **Focus** \| Future, big picture \| Present, details \|
M|Role|tx|\| **Strength** \| Ideas, relationships, culture \| Execution, accountability, alignment \|
M|Role|tx|\| **Energy** \| Inspires and energizes \| Organizes and stabilizes \|
M|Role|tx|\| **Meetings** \| Often bored in operational meetings \| Runs the Level 10 meeting \|
M|Role|tx|\| **Decisions** \| Makes 10 decisions, 7 are great \| Makes fewer decisions, all well-considered \|
M|Role|tx|\| **People** \| Attracts talent \| Develops and manages talent \|
M|Role|tx|\| **Conflict** \| May avoid hard conversations \| Resolves conflict directly \|
M|The |1. *|** gn new pd, markets, and strategies
M|The |2. *|** Set the tone, md core values
M|The |3. *|** Manage top cs, partners, industry connections
M|The |4. *|** Tackle the company's biggest challenges
M|The |5. *|** Close major deals and evangelize the company
M|The |1. *|** Manage day-to-day operations
M|The |2. *|** Facilitate meetings, hold leaders accountable
M|The |3. *|** Translate vision into quarterly and weekly action
M|The |4. *|** Break ties, mediate disputes, make hard calls
M|The |5. *|** Evaluate which ideas to pursue and which to shelve
M|The |**He|**
M|The |it|[ ] They meet weekly for a 30-60 minute "Same Page Meeting"
M|The |it|[ ] The Visionary shares ideas freely; the Integrator evaluates and filters
M|The |it|[ ] The Integrator has authority to run the business w/o daily Visionary approval
M|The |it|[ ] Disagreements are resolved privately, not in front of the team
M|The |it|[ ] Both publicly support each other's decisions
M|The |**Un|**
M|The |it|The Visionary micromanages the Integrator
M|The |it|The Integrator blocks all new ideas
M|The |it|They contradict each other in team meetings
M|The |it|Neither is willing to let the other lead in their domain
