M|The |The |core values fit (Right Person) and role fit (Right Seat).
M|Scor|**St|Rate Core Values**
M|Scor|For |
M|Scor|tx|\| Symbol \| Meaning \| Description \|
M|Scor|tx|\|--------\|---------\|-------------\|
M|Scor|tx|\| **+** \| Most of the time \| Exhibits this value consistently (80%+) \|
M|Scor|tx|\| **+/-** \| Sometimes \| Exhibits this value inconsistently (50-80%) \|
M|Scor|tx|\| **-** \| Rarely \| Does not exhibit this value (<50%) \|
M|Scor|**Th|** Everyone must be "+" on every core value. One "+/-" is a coaching conversation w/ a 90-day deadline to improve. Two "+/-" or any "-" means this is the wrong person.
M|Peop|tx|\| Name \| Core Value 1 \| Core Value 2 \| Core Value 3 \| Core Value 4 \| GWC \| Decision \|
M|Peop|tx|\|------\|-------------\|-------------\|-------------\|-------------\|-----\|----------\|
M|Peop|tx|\| Sarah \| + \| + \| + \| + \| Y/Y/Y \| Keep (A-player) \|
M|Peop|tx|\| James \| + \| +/- \| + \| + \| Y/Y/Y \| Coach (90-day plan) \|
M|Peop|tx|\| Priya \| + \| + \| + \| + \| Y/N/Y \| Move seat \|
M|Peop|tx|\| Dave \| - \| +/- \| + \| + \| Y/Y/Y \| Exit \|
M|Peop|tx|\| Lisa \| + \| + \| + \| + \| Y/Y/N \| Develop or move \|
M|GWC |tx|GWC stands for Get it, Want it, Capacity to do it. All three must be "yes" for someone to be in the right seat.
M|Get |tx|Does this person truly understand the role? Not just the tasks, but the nuances, the judgment calls, the unwritten rules. Someone who "gets it" can anticipate problems, see connections, and make decisions w/o being told.
M|Get |**Di|**
M|Get |it|Can they explain the role's purpose in one sentence?
M|Get |it|Do they see the downstream impact of their decisions?
M|Get |it|Do they need constant direction, or do they figure things out?
M|Want|tx|Does this person genuinely want this specific role? Not a paycheck. Not a title. This actual work, every day. People who "want it" show up w/ energy for the role, not just tolerance.
M|Want|**Di|**
M|Want|it|wld they choose this role if money were not a factor?
M|Want|it|Do they light up when talking abt their work?
M|Want|it|Are they making sacrifices willingly, or resentfully?
M|Capa|tx|Does this person have the intellectual, physical, emotional, and time capacity to excel? Capacity is the hardest to change. Skills can be trained. Capacity is more fundamental.
M|Capa|**Di|**
M|Capa|it|Can they handle the volume and complexity of the role?
M|Capa|it|Do they have the emotional resilience the role requires?
M|Capa|it|Are they already at capacity, or do they have room to grow into the role?
M|GWC |tx|\| G \| W \| C \| Verdict \| Action \|
M|GWC |tx|\|---\|---\|---\|---------\|--------\|
M|GWC |tx|\| Y \| Y \| Y \| Right seat \| Invest and retain \|
M|GWC |tx|\| Y \| Y \| N \| Capacity gap \| Train, reduce scope, or move \|
M|GWC |tx|\| Y \| N \| Y \| Motivation issue \| Have honest conversation, likely move seats \|
M|GWC |tx|\| Y \| N \| N \| Wrong seat entirely \| Move to a different seat \|
M|GWC |tx|\| N \| Y \| Y \| Doesn't get it \| Coach for 90 days, may not be fixable \|
M|GWC |tx|\| N \| Y \| N \| Square peg, round hole \| Move seats \|
M|GWC |tx|\| N \| N \| Y \| Capable but wrong fit \| Find the seat they get and want \|
M|GWC |tx|\| N \| N \| N \| Wrong seat \| Move immediately \|
M|Righ|tx|\| \| Right Seat \| Wrong Seat \|
M|Righ|tx|\|---\|-----------\|------------\|
M|Righ|tx|\| **Right Person** \| A-player. Protect, invest, promote. \| Move to the right seat. They share your values -- find where they thrive. \|
M|Righ|tx|\| **Wrong Person** \| Hardest call. They produce results but damage culture. The answer is almost always exit. \| Exit. No fit on either dimension. Delay makes it worse. \|
M|The |This|
M|The |1. *|** Direct conversation. "Here is the core value you are violating, here is the specific behavior, here is what needs to change."
M|The |2. *|** Written 30-day improvement plan w/ specific behavioral milestones.
M|The |3. *|** Exit. The team is watching. Keeping a wrong person teaches everyone that core values are negotiable.
M|Prep|it|[ ] Write down the specific issue w/ concrete examples
M|Prep|it|[ ] Identify which core value or GWC element is in question
M|Prep|it|[ ] Choose a private setting w/ no interruptions
M|Prep|it|[ ] Plan to listen more than talk (60/40 rule)
M|Prep|it|[ ] Have a clear outcome in mind (coaching plan, role change, or exit)
M|The |tx|1. **State the issue directly.** "I need to talk abt [specific behavior/perf]. This is important for both of us."
M|The |tx|2. **Give specific examples.** "On [date], [what happened]. Last week, [another example]."
M|The |tx|3. **Connect to core values or GWC.** "This conflicts w/ our core value of [value]" or "I'm concerned abt your capacity for [specific aspect]."
M|The |4. *|"What's your perspective?" Listen w/o interrupting.
M|The |tx|5. **Agree on nx steps.** "Here's what needs to change, by when, and how we'll measure it."
M|The |tx|6. **Document.** Confirm the conversation and commitments in writing within 24 hours.
M|Inte|**St|Screen for core values first.** Before evaluating skills, assess whether the candidate aligns w/ each core value.
M|Inte|**St|Use behavioral questions tied to each core value.**
M|Inte|tx|\| Core Value \| Interview Question \|
M|Inte|tx|\|-----------\|-------------------\|
M|Inte|tx|\| Own It \| "Tell me abt a time you made a mistake at work. What happened and what did you do?" \|
M|Inte|tx|\| Do the Right Thing \| "Describe a situation where you had to choose btw what was easy and what was right." \|
M|Inte|tx|\| Grow or Die \| "What's the last skill you taught yourself? How did you go abt it?" \|
M|Inte|**St|Back-channel references.** Ask references specifically abt core values behaviors, not just competence.
M|Inte|**St|Trial period.** The first 90 days are an extended interview. Evaluate core values fit at 30, 60, and 90 days.
M|Quar|Ever|
M|Quar|tx|\| Section \| Time \| Focus \|
M|Quar|tx|\|---------\|------\|-------\|
M|Quar|tx|\| Core Values rv \| 10 min \| Rate each value (+, +/-, -). Discuss any +/- w/ specific examples. Acknowledge strengths. \|
M|Quar|tx|\| GWC Check \| 10 min \| Get it (clear on role?), Want it (still energized?), Capacity (right-sized workload?) \|
M|Quar|tx|\| Rock rv \| 5 min \| On track / off track. What support is needed? \|
M|Quar|tx|\| Forward Look \| 5 min \| nx quarter outlook, dv goals, feedback for the leader \|
